page.title: 01Landscape and buildings
page.content:
We were assigned to this area as part of a three day enviromental studies couse.
As it is some miles from our own school and homes our study has been a rather limited one.
Most of the area is very thinly populated except for a few fairly large houses on the outskirts of Yarmouth (the fringe of our study area).
There is only one very small village (or hamlet) in the area. This is Wellow which we could not find mentioned in the main guide books of the area.
